            </xs:annotation>
          </xs:element>
        </xs:sequence>
      </xs:complexType>
      <xs:simpleType name="SessionState1">
        <xs:annotation>
          <xs:documentation>&lt;p&gt;The state of the session. A description of each state follows.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;code&gt;CREATING&lt;/code&gt; - The session is being started, including acquiring resources.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;code&gt;CREATED&lt;/code&gt; - The session has been started.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;code&gt;IDLE&lt;/code&gt; - The session is able to accept a calculation.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;code&gt;BUSY&lt;/code&gt; - The session is processing another task and is unable to accept a calculation.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;code&gt;TERMINATING&lt;/code&gt; - The session is in the process of shutting down.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;code&gt;TERMINATED&lt;/code&gt; - The session and its resources are no longer running.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;code&gt;DEGRADED&lt;/code&gt; - The session has no healthy coordinators.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;code&gt;FAILED&lt;/code&gt; - Due to a failure, the session and its resources are no longer running.&lt;/p&gt;</xs:documentation>
        </xs:annotation>
        <xs:restriction base="xs:string">
          <xs:enumeration value="CREATING" />
